SHONGWE – Two people died and one is seriously injured when a bus and a bakkie collided  this morning on the Langeloop main road.  According to the Department of Community, Safety and Security spokesman Joseph Mabuza, the accident happened at around 07:00. He said the two people who had died had been occupants of the bakkie. “There were also 10 people who were slightly injured, they have all been taken to Shongwe hospital.” 